#limitation(title: [PEM Vicious Cycle Model: Illustrative Framework, Not Quantified Biology])[
The vicious cycle dynamics model below (cycle gain, sequential entry, ratchet effect) provides a conceptually useful framework for understanding disease progression, but its quantitative parameters are illustrative, not empirically derived:

    - Numerical values for "cycle gain" (5–10% vs.\ 30–50% ATP reduction per iteration), "repair capacity" (15–20% biogenesis rate), and "critical thresholds" are hypothetical estimates chosen to illustrate the model's logic, not measurements from ME/CFS patients.
    - The distinction between "escapable" and "inescapable" cycles has not been validated by longitudinal studies tracking cycle parameters over time in individual patients.
    - Whether ME/CFS progression truly follows a sequential cycle-recruitment pattern or reflects a single initial insult with variable downstream consequences is undetermined.
    - The model's predictions (earlier intervention = better outcomes, cycle number predicts severity) are consistent with clinical observation but have not been prospectively tested.

]
